---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Project Dossier">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="blueprint-grid-hero">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12 sm:py-16">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-10 lg:gap-12 items-center">
        <!-- Left: Text (3 columns) -->
        <div class="lg:col-span-3">
          <span class="badge mb-4 inline-block">Closed Beta</span>
          <h1 class="text-stone-900 mb-4">Open Working Hours</h1>
          <p class="text-xl text-stone-600 mb-4">
            Privacy-preserving infrastructure for documenting and aggregating healthcare working conditions.
          </p>
          <a href="/dashboard" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-teal-600 hover:text-teal-700 font-medium text-sm">
            See current coverage across Germany →
          </a>
        </div>

        <!-- Right: Phone Mockup (2 columns) -->
        <div class="lg:col-span-2 flex justify-center lg:justify-end">
          <div class="phone-mockup-small">
            <div class="phone-screen">
              <img
                src="/screenshots/status-dashboard.png"
                alt="Status Dashboard showing 14-day work hours overview"
              />
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Problem Statement -->
  <section class="section-alt py-12 sm:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h2 class="text-stone-900 mb-4">Problem</h2>
        <div class="prose text-stone-700 space-y-4">
          <p>
            Workload in German hospitals regularly exceeds legal limits in many areas.<a href="#ref-1" class="footnote" title="Working Hours Act (ArbZG), § 3">[1]</a>
          </p>
          <p>
            Medical and nursing staff systematically work overtime, often without complete documentation.<a href="#ref-2" class="footnote" title="Marburger Bund: Violations of working time documentation">[2]</a><a href="#ref-3" class="footnote" title="Deutsches Ärzteblatt: University clinics and time tracking">[3]</a>
          </p>
          <p>
            The consequences are documented:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li>Elevated burnout rates and attrition of skilled workers<a href="#ref-4" class="footnote" title="WSI-Mitteilungen: Working conditions of nursing staff">[4]</a><a href="#ref-5" class="footnote" title="BARMER Nursing Study 2.0">[5]</a></li>
            <li>Increased risk of medical errors – including preventable ones<a href="#ref-6" class="footnote" title="Medical Service: Treatment error statistics">[6]</a></li>
            <li>Longer wait times and reduced quality of care for patients<a href="#ref-7" class="footnote" title="DKG: Staff shortage">[7]</a></li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            <em>These conditions are widely known. Yet structural change remains absent.</em>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Analysis -->
  <section class="py-12 sm:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h2 class="text-stone-900 mb-4">Analysis</h2>
        <div class="prose text-stone-700 space-y-4">
          <p>
            Hospitals operate under considerable economic pressure.<a href="#ref-8" class="footnote" title="DKI: Hospital Barometer 2025">[8]</a><a href="#ref-9" class="footnote" title="DKG: Economic situation of hospitals">[9]</a> A common response is to reduce staffing costs, leading to chronic understaffing.<a href="#ref-8" class="footnote" title="DKI: Hospital Barometer 2025">[8]</a><a href="#ref-10" class="footnote" title="BDO & DKI: Staff shortage in hospitals">[10]</a>
          </p>
          <p>
            In functioning systems, corrective mechanisms exist for such failures:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li><strong>Market mechanisms</strong> (where choices exist): Patients and skilled workers choose other institutions, creating economic pressure for change.</li>
            <li><strong>Legal mechanisms:</strong> Violations of working time regulations or liability cases for treatment errors lead to sanctions that alter decision-makers' calculations.<a href="#ref-1" class="footnote" title="Working Hours Act (ArbZG), § 3">[1]</a><a href="#ref-11" class="footnote" title="Federal Labor Court: Obligation to record working hours">[11]</a><a href="#ref-6" class="footnote" title="Medical Service: Treatment error statistics">[6]</a></li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            However, both mechanisms require that the underlying problems are visible and demonstrable.
          </p>
          <p>
            Here lies the central bottleneck: Actual workload is often not fully, independently, and comparably documented.<a href="#ref-2" class="footnote" title="Marburger Bund: Violations of working time documentation">[2]</a><a href="#ref-3" class="footnote" title="Deutsches Ärzteblatt: University clinics and time tracking">[3]</a><a href="#ref-11" class="footnote" title="Federal Labor Court: Obligation to record working hours">[11]</a>
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 ml-4">
            <li>Without reliable data, there is no basis for evidence.</li>
            <li>Without evidence, no pressure for action.</li>
            <li>Without pressure, no correction.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Solution -->
  <section class="section-alt py-12 sm:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h2 class="text-stone-900 mb-4">Approach</h2>
        <div class="prose text-stone-700 space-y-4">
          <p>
            The bottleneck described above can be addressed through systematic transparency.
          </p>
          <p>
            This platform enables healthcare workers to record their working hours on their own device and contribute anonymously to aggregated statistics.
          </p>
          <p>
            No personal data is published – only aggregated, anonymized metrics at the institutional level, released only when a minimum number of contributors is reached.
          </p>
          <p>
            The principle:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-4">
            <li><strong>Protect individuals:</strong> Workers should not face additional disadvantages or risks for documenting overwork.</li>
            <li><strong>Make institutional responsibility visible:</strong> Responsibility for working conditions should rest with decision-makers who determine staffing and organizational structures.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            The resulting data can serve as an evidence base:
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-1 ml-4">
            <li>In collective bargaining</li>
            <li>In health policy debates</li>
            <li>Where necessary: in legal proceedings</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Solution Details -->
        <div class="mt-6 space-y-2 text-stone-700">
          <p><strong>Product:</strong> iOS app for recording actual working hours – automatically via geofencing or manually in seconds.</p>
          <p><strong>Target group:</strong> Physicians, nurses, and healthcare workers who want to contribute to transparency.</p>
          <p><strong>Output:</strong> Aggregated, anonymized statistics – by region, specialty, and role level.</p>
          <p><strong>Status:</strong> iOS app in closed beta. Backend deployed. Seeking pilot partners.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Principles -->
  <section class="py-12 sm:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h2 class="text-stone-900 mb-4">Principles</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-stone-700">
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-teal-600 mt-1">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
              </svg>
            </span>
            <span><strong>Low friction:</strong> Automatic tracking via geofencing. Manual entry in seconds.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-teal-600 mt-1">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
              </svg>
            </span>
            <span><strong>Not an employer tool:</strong> Data belongs to users. No third-party access.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-teal-600 mt-1">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
              </svg>
            </span>
            <span><strong>Privacy by design:</strong> Individual data never published. Only aggregated statistics with k-anonymity.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-teal-600 mt-1">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
              </svg>
            </span>
            <span><strong>Full control:</strong> Data export and deletion anytime. GDPR compliant.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Evidence Links -->
  <section class="border-t border-stone-200 py-8">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <h3 class="text-stone-500 text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-wide mb-4">Learn more</h3>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-x-8 gap-y-2 text-stone-700">
        <a href="/product" class="hover:text-teal-600">View product demo</a>
        <a href="/privacy" class="hover:text-teal-600">Read privacy principles</a>
        <a href="/team" class="hover:text-teal-600">Team & Contact</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Sources -->
  <section class="border-t border-stone-200 py-8 bg-stone-50">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <h3 class="text-stone-500 text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-wide mb-4">Sources</h3>
      <ol class="text-sm text-stone-600 space-y-2 list-decimal list-inside">
        <li id="ref-1">Working Hours Act (ArbZG), § 3 – Working hours of employees. <a href="https://www.gesetze-im-internet.de/arbzg/__3.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-teal-600 hover:underline">Gesetze-im-Internet</a></li>
        <li id="ref-2">Marburger Bund: "Massive violations by university clinics against working time documentation requirements…" (25.06.2025). <a href="https://www.marburger-bund.de/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-teal-600 hover:underline">marburger-bund.de</a></li>
        <li id="ref-3">Deutsches Ärzteblatt: "Majority of university clinics violate working time documentation" (25.06.2025). <a href="https://www.aerzteblatt.de/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-teal-600 hover:underline">aerzteblatt.de</a></li>
        <li id="ref-4">WSI-Mitteilungen: "Working conditions, health and exhaustion among nursing staff in Germany" (Analysis based on BIBB/BAuA employment survey). <a href="https://www.wsi.de/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-teal-600 hover:underline">wsi.de</a></li>
        <li id="ref-5">BARMER: "Nursing Study 2.0" – Resource and stress analysis for nursing staff (2023). <a href="https://www.barmer.de/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-teal-600 hover:underline">barmer.de</a></li>
        <li id="ref-6">Medical Service Germany: Annual statistics on treatment error assessments (2024) / Press release (30.10.2025). <a href="https://www.md-bund.de/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-teal-600 hover:underline">md-bund.de</a></li>
        <li id="ref-7">German Hospital Federation (DKG): "Hospital association demands decisive action against staff shortage" (12.10.2025). <a href="https://www.dkgev.de/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-teal-600 hover:underline">dkgev.de</a></li>
        <li id="ref-8">DKI: "Hospital Barometer 2025" (29.12.2025). <a href="https://www.dki.de/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-teal-600 hover:underline">dki.de</a></li>
        <li id="ref-9">DKG: "Many hospitals fighting for survival" – Press on economic situation (29.12.2025). <a href="https://www.dkgev.de/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-teal-600 hover:underline">dkgev.de</a></li>
        <li id="ref-10">BDO & DKI: "Staff shortage in hospitals – Quo vadis?" (Study, 2024). <a href="https://www.bdo.de/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-teal-600 hover:underline">bdo.de</a></li>
        <li id="ref-11">Federal Labor Court (BAG): Decision 1 ABR 22/21 – Obligation to record working hours (13.09.2022) + BMAS FAQ. <a href="https://www.bmas.de/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-teal-600 hover:underline">bmas.de</a></li>
      </ol>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
